                            <comment id="12844550" author="kovyrin" created="Fri, 12 Mar 2010 15:54:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to add a get_counter &apos;table&apos;, &apos;column&apos; command that would decode the counter and print its value.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12844553" author="stack" created="Fri, 12 Mar 2010 16:01:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent.  I said get_counter because I thought that rubyesque.  Feel free to make it something else if you have a better idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12844813" author="kovyrin" created="Sat, 13 Mar 2010 06:04:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; Added get_counter shell command + improved incr command (now it shows the result of an increment)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12844814" author="kovyrin" created="Sat, 13 Mar 2010 06:07:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch submitted to implement get_counter command and improve incr command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;~/work/git/hbase (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2314&quot; title=&quot;[shell] Support for getting counters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;01:05&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; $ ./bin/hbase shell&lt;br/&gt;
HBase Shell; enter &apos;help&amp;lt;RETURN&amp;gt;&apos; for list of supported commands.&lt;br/&gt;
Type &quot;exit&amp;lt;RETURN&amp;gt;&quot; to leave the HBase Shell&lt;br/&gt;
Version: 0.21.0-SNAPSHOT, rUnknown, Tue Mar  9 23:15:28 EST 2010&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):001:0&amp;gt; get &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
COLUMN                       CELL                                                                             &lt;br/&gt;
0 row(s) in 0.4100 seconds&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):002:0&amp;gt; get_counter &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
No counter found at specified coordinates&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):003:0&amp;gt; incr &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;       &lt;br/&gt;
COUNTER VALUE = 1&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):004:0&amp;gt; get_counter &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
COUNTER VALUE = 1&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):005:0&amp;gt; incr &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;       &lt;br/&gt;
COUNTER VALUE = 2&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):006:0&amp;gt; incr &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
COUNTER VALUE = 3&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):007:0&amp;gt; get_counter &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
COUNTER VALUE = 3&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):008:0&amp;gt; get &apos;blah&apos;, 123, &apos;a:cnt&apos;        &lt;br/&gt;
COLUMN                       CELL                                                                             &lt;br/&gt;
 a:cnt                       timestamp=1268460380431, value=\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x03                  &lt;br/&gt;
1 row(s) in 0.0210 seconds&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):009:0&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12844960" author="stack" created="Sat, 13 Mar 2010 20:33:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All shell tests pass.  I ran ./bin/hbase shell-tests.  Committed to TRUNK. Thanks for the patch Alexey.  Its how now new commands are self-contained and its just about adding a new file to support new functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
